Ondo State Commissioner for Information and Orientation, Honourable Donald Ojogo resigns amidst growing support for his aspiration to contest as a Member, House of Representatives (Ilaje/Ese-Odo Federal Constituency). His resignation takes effect from Thursday, April 14, 2022. In the letter sighted by DAILY INDEPENDENT, Ojogo appreciated Governor Rotimi Akeredolu, SAN, for the support so far while assuring that their journey of political bonding has just begun.